Definition: produced under conditions involving intense heat
Example: igneous rock is rock formed by solidification from a molten state; especially from molten magma; igneous fusion is fusion by heat alone; pyrogenic strata
Synonyms: noun, attribute, heat, pyrogenic, pyrogenous, produced, under, conditions, involving, intense, rock, is, formed, by, solidification, from, a, molten, state, especially, magma, fusion, alone, strata
Category: adj.pert
